Installation Instructions
----------------------------


For Windows Platforms
----------------------

Prior to attempting to run Boris the first time, please install the VisualC++ runtime. A copy of the installation file can be found at this location:

{Boris Project Root}\Build\Win32\

A pre-built binary can be downloaded from the following location:

The folder Boris, contained within the above zip file has all the required dependencies and files. To install the game, simply copy this folder to a desired location on the hard disk.

Should you need to rebuild the solution, please use the Visual C++ solution file included with the source code -- {Boris Project Root}\Project Files\VC. Please note that the solution file was created using Visual C++ 2010, and you will need to install that software (Or a later version) in order to use it.

A free copy can be obtained from the following location:
http://www.microsoft.com/express/windows/


For Unix Platforms
----------------------

Boris was succesfully installed and tested on the following Unix-like systems:

Ubunto 32-bit 10.4 

Due to the great variety of Unix-like systems in existance, this project is not pre-packaged with any pre-built binary files. Instead, it is recommended that you build the game from source using the provided SCons scripts. In order to do so, please make sure that you have the following components installed on your system -- Many of them are pre-packaged with most linux distributions, in the case of Debian or Red Hat systems, it is reccommended that you use the package installation facilities:

python 2.6 or later: http://www.python.org/download/
scons 1.3 or later: http://www.scons.org/download.php
sdl 1.2 or later: http://www.libsdl.org/download-1.2.php
sdl-mixer 1.2.10 or later: http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_mixer/
sdl-ttf 1.2.10 or later: http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_mixer/
lua 5.1 or later: http://www.lua.org/download.html
libvorbis 1.2 or later: http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/blfs/view/stable/multimedia/libvorbis.html

Then open the terminal and navigate to the following location:

{Boris Project Root}\Boris


To create a binary package in the build directory -- {Boris Project Root}\Boris\Build\Scons -- run the following command:

scons

To copy the files to the usr/local/bin folder, run the following command:

scons install


